<p>I’ve just started working on a <a href="https://github.com/placemark/figma-plugin" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Figma plugin under the Placemark name</a>
that makes a certain kind of map possible within Figma for (I think) the first
time - a purely vector-based, fully open source and open data plugin.
You could say it’s 1% of <a href="https://www.avenza.com/mapublisher/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">MAPublisher</a>,
for 0% of the price. I’m not sure where that experiment will go, but I’ll
have a use for it in my own projects and it’s nicely scoped so that
it can just be open source &amp; server-free for the time being.</p>
